A 59-year-old woman died after being run over by a private bus recently roped in to provide services during the odd-even scheme.The victim, an accountant with the Ministry of AYUSH, was travelling to her office in Lodhi Road at the time of the accident. Her husband was driving the scooter when they were hit. Chander Kochcharâ€™s husband sustained multiple injuries and is undergoing treatment at AIIMS trauma centre, where he is said to be stable.The accident took place around 10 a.m. on Thursday in Nehru Place. The couple was near the Paras Cinema flyover when their scooter was hit by the bus. The woman, who fell off and came under the wheels of the bus, died on the spot.